How can I specify the geometry of the dialog in qt mode?
========================================================

   Start dldialog with the -geometry in the EXTRA OPTIONS section. E.g.:
     $ dldialog -q -- -geometry 640x480 << EOF
     dialog "TEST" {
         text "TEST";
         button "&OK" -exit;
     }
     EOF


File: dldialog.info,  Node: How can I change elements depending on others?,  Next: How can I configure my xterm to display nice colours?,  Prev: How can I specify the geometry of the dialog in qt mode?,  Up: Questions and answers

How can I change elements depending on others?
==============================================

   Suppose you want to get the host name and domain name of a host. You
want to preset the domain name with the domain of the host name, once
the user has entered it.
     #!/bin/sh
     
     # Start the server
     result=$(dldialog --start $@)
     eval "$result"
     export DLDIALOG_INFIFO
     
     export OK="0";
     
     while [ "$OK" != "1" ]; do
     
       result=$(dldialog <<EOF
       dialog "Maindialog" {
         hostname="$hostname";
         domain="$domain";
         text "";
           row {
             col {
               text "Hostname:";
               text "Domainname:";
             }
             col {
               input -var hostname -length 20 -exit;
               input -var domain -length 20;
             }
           }
           button "&OK" -var OK -set "1" -exit;
       }
     EOF)
     
       eval "$result"
     
       if [ -z "$domain" ]; then
         export domain=`echo $hostname|(IFS='.' read a b;echo $b)`;
       fi
     
     done
     
     dldialog --wait

   `Note:' The user has to press return after entering the hostname to
let the dialog exit.


