Why can't I see my list?
========================

   If no -width and -height is specified the element shows up with it's
smallest size.

   Remember: -width and -height are relative to the element with the
most inner {}. The dialog element's width and height tags are relative
to the -geometry size (or as a default 600x400).

   Specifying -width and -height also gives dldialog a hint which
elements have to grow how much, if the dialog resizes.

   This one is ugly:
     dialog "Not so nice" {
       list "A very small list" {
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
       }
     }

   Here a nicer one:
     dialog "Not so nice" -width 100 -height 100 {
       list "A very small list" -width 100 -height 100 {
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
         listitem "Item";
       }
     }


